URI::Signature::Tiny

This is a minimal helper to generate URLs that you can later verify to
not have been modified, so that you can trust security-relevant values
such as user IDs. This is useful e.g. for a passwort reset link that the
user should not be able to edit to log in as someone else.

INSTALLATION

This is a Perl module distribution. It should be installed with whichever
tool you use to manage your installation of Perl, e.g. any of

  cpanm .
  cpan  .
  cpanp -i .

Consult http://www.cpan.org/modules/INSTALL.html for further instruction.
Should you wish to install this module manually, the procedure is

  perl Makefile.PL
  make
  make test
  make install

